title: 9 Sex Things An Average Guy "Learned" About Sex From Fifty Shades Darker
text:
In the interest of full disclosure, I think Fifty Shades Darker is a garbage movie for trash babies. But even flaming, putrid wrecks can teach people things. Similarly to how watching a car full of old refuse smash into a concrete barrier at 100 miles an hour is a great way to learn how not to drive.
Advertisement - Continue Reading Below 1. Handcuffs and spanking are crazy kinky, apparently. To be fair, Christian Grey has an entire room devoted to sex, which is a red flag by itself (although, when you’re as rich as he is you probably have enough living space that you run out of things to do with it). But it seems like in every example, all he really wants to do is tie Ana up and spank her a bit. And it’s a huge point of contention. I can’t imagine what would happen if he wanted to put on a fur-suit and seal Ana in latex.
